      "memo": "Custody-by-key at the enterprise level typically involves no export control issues, focusing on commercial data protection rather than controlled items.",
      "detail": "No control issue means the custody architecture is applied to commercially valuable but uncontrolled data and capability. This keeps the stance focused on the fundamental custody-by-key principle without complicating it with export control overlay. The architecture works equally well for controlled items but the core argument is cleaner without that complexity. No control exposure allows the custody analysis to focus purely on the architectural strength comparison."
    },
