      "detail": "Inference processing means the key controls access to model use without requiring access to training data or model internals. This separation of use-authorization from data-custody is a key strength of the custody-by-key architecture. The key holder can grant inference access without transferring custody of underlying data or model weights. Inference-mode key gating demonstrates the custody essay's claim that use can be separated from possession."
    },
